The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the construction of non-crossing spanning trees in a geometric complete bipartite graph. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves combinatorial aspects, such as the maximum degree of the tree, which suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. The problem is related to graph theory, which makes cs.GT (Graph Theory) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for solving the problem, which could make it relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
